00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Job interviews can feel stressful, especially in English. Today, you'll master essential phrases that will help you introduce yourself professionally, describe your experience, and answer common interview questions with confidence.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:30.000
In this lesson, we'll cover four essential interview skills:

First, introducing yourself professionally.
Second, describing your experience and achievements.
Third, answering common interview questions effectively.
And fourth, asking intelligent questions that impress interviewers.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:40.000
These skills will help you succeed in any job interview and make a strong professional impression.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Let's start with introducing yourself professionally. The interviewer might ask: 'Tell me about yourself' or 'Can you introduce yourself?'

This is your first impression. Make it count.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Here's a professional introduction structure:

**Start with your current role or education**:
'I'm currently working as [position] at [company].'
'I'm a [position] with [X] years of experience.'

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:30.000
**Highlight your key strengths**:
'I specialize in [area of expertise].'
'My strengths include [skill 1], [skill 2], and [skill 3].'

**Express interest in the position**:
'I'm very interested in this position because [reason].'

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Let me show you a complete professional introduction:

'Hi, I'm [Your Name]. I'm currently working as a [position] at [company], where I've been for [X] years. I specialize in [area], and my strengths include [skill 1] and [skill 2].'

00:01:45.000 --> 00:02:00.000
'I'm very interested in this position because [reason]. I'm excited about the opportunity to [contribution].'

Practice this structure until it feels natural.

